defaultThe 
defaultDengie Peninsula is a particularly remote and isolated area of rural Essex, 
defaultbounded
default by 
defaultthe sea to the east and the Blackwater and Crouch rivers to the north and south.  The low population density and isolated nature of the area make provision of convention
defaultal bus services difficult, having lost most of its commercial operations since 1985 and the county council increasingly having had to contract services. 
default**
defaultA DRT scheme is a taxi-bus service which operates a core 
defaultroute but can be booked in advance to pick 
defaultup from a passenger’s house from outlying areas. Services can be timetabled or fully flexible within an operating period.
