default3.1 
defaultWith regards to
default buses, by their nature isolated rural areas have small populations whose travel needs are not easily aggregated into a financially sustainable commercial bus network. Contracted bus services can easily become unsusta
defaulti
defaultnable 
defaultdue to demographic shifts or rising costs. 
default In addition, i
defaultt is 
defaultmore difficult to manoeuvre
default large buses
default around narrow lanes where potential additional passengers may be (who are unable to get to the main route)
default. 
defaultEven DRT is made less sustainable due 
defaultto the high levels
default of dead mileage and escalating
default fares impacting on demand. Therefore public transport in these areas will always require public funding support in on
defaulte sense or another. Within this
default, kick-starting DRT services ( and thus removing some or a
defaultll of the entry cost barrier to service provision)  is possibly a better approach than long term service purchasing, if sufficient attention is paid to the marketing and organisational structure of the services. Either CT or taxi services can in theory mak
defaulte use of this approach, but in either case an excellent understanding of the potential market and its needs is necessary.
default Flexibility is a key factor, and the ability to call in additional vehicles (as the Essex DRT scheme is run by a taxi company) has pro
defaultved invaluable.
